  "chapter": {
    "number": 37,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Delight Yourself in the LORD"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "hebrew_subtitle",
        "content": [
          "Of David.",
          {
            "noteId": 4356
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Do not fret over those who do evil;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "do not envy those who do wrong.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For they wither quickly like grass",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and wilt like tender plants.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Trust in the LORD and do good;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "dwell in the land and cultivate faithfulness.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Delight yourself in the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and He will give you the desires of your heart.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Commit your way to the LORD;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "trust in Him, and He will do it.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He will bring forth your righteousness like the dawn,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "your justice like the noonday sun.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Be still before the LORD",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and wait patiently for Him;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "do not fret when men prosper in their ways,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "when they carry out wicked schemes.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Refrain from anger and abandon wrath;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "do not fretâ€”it can only bring harm.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For the evildoers will be cut off,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but those who hope in the LORD will inherit the land.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Yet a little while, and the wicked will be no more;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "though you look for them, they will not be found.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But the meek will inherit the land",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4357
          },
          {
            "text": "and delight in abundant prosperity.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The wicked scheme against the righteous",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and gnash their teeth at them,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "but the Lord laughs,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "seeing that their day is coming.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The wicked have drawn the sword",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and bent the bow",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "to bring down the poor and needy,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to slay those whose ways are upright.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But their swords will pierce their own hearts,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and their bows will be broken.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Better is the little of the righteous",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "than the abundance of many who are wicked.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For the arms of the wicked will be broken,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the LORD upholds the righteous.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The LORD knows the days of the blameless,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and their inheritance will last forever.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "In the time of evil they will not be ashamed,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and in the days of famine they will be satisfied.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But the wicked and enemies of the LORD",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will perish like the glory of the fields.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They will vanish;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like smoke they will fade away.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The wicked borrow and do not repay,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the righteous are gracious and giving.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Surely those He blesses will inherit the land,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the cursed will be destroyed.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The steps of a man are ordered by the LORD",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who takes delight in his journey.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Though he falls, he will not be overwhelmed,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for the LORD is holding his hand.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4358
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I once was young and now am old,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "yet never have I seen the righteous abandoned",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "or their children begging for bread.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They are ever generous and quick to lend,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and their children are a blessing.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 27,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Turn away from evil and do good,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so that you will abide forever.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 28,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For the LORD loves justice",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and will not forsake His saints.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They are preserved forever,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the offspring of the wicked will be cut off.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 29,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The righteous will inherit the land",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and dwell in it forever.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 30,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The mouth of the righteous man utters wisdom,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and his tongue speaks justice.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 31,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The law of his God is in his heart;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "his steps do not falter.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 32,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Though the wicked lie in wait for the righteous,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and seek to slay them,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 33,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "the LORD will not leave them in their power",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or let them be condemned under judgment.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 34,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Wait for the LORD and keep His way,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and He will raise you up to inherit the land.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "When the wicked are cut off,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you will see it.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 35,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I have seen a wicked, ruthless man",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "flourishing like a well-rooted native tree,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 36,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "yet he passed away and was no more;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "though I searched, he could not be found.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 37,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Consider the blameless and observe the upright,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for posterity awaits the man of peace.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4359
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 38,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But the transgressors will all be destroyed;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the future of the wicked will be cut off.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 39,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The salvation of the righteous is from the LORD;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He is their stronghold in time of trouble.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 40,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The LORD helps and delivers them;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He rescues and saves them from the wicked,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "because they take refuge in Him.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
        "noteId": 4356,
